# Boot Manual — Atelier Engine v0.1

End-to-end runbook for the three deployment paths Atelier supports today. Active beta cut: **v0.1-beta-2** (BYO-infra Market Data Collection, Iteration 4.x). This file evolves in place — for iteration cadence and what's currently in flight, see `engineering-notes.md`. For the success criteria the platform is shipping against, see `product-notes.md`.

| Path | Audience | Outcome |
|---|---|---|
| **A · Local Dev** | Engineer working on the platform | Single-machine stack: backend + webapp + agent on `localhost`. Fastest iteration loop. |
| **B · Production Hosting** | Operator standing up `iteralabs.xyz/atelier` (webapp) + `/atelier/docs` (MkDocs) for an alive demo | One Docker image (SPA + MkDocs + nginx) behind Cloudflare Tunnel; backend runs alongside on the same host. |
| **C · End-User Agent** | Researcher who got credentials from the webapp and wants to start collecting data | Single `docker run` on their own machine; data lands as Parquet on local disk; appears live in the dashboard. |

**Iteration status snapshot (2026-05-12).** 4.1 / 4.2 / 4.3 / 4.4 shipped end-to-end (live verified via `accept_w4a.sh` + `accept_i4_4.sh`). 4.5 partial — Parquet writes work and ArtifactFrames reach Kafka, but lineage rows in `artifacts` table are blocked on the cross-process `task_id` allocation gap. 4.6 + 4.7 are the active closeout (see `engineering-notes.md`). For the demo, the user-visible loop (use-case steps 1–6) works; lineage persistence does not until 4.6 lands.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[1·Clean] --> B[2·Config] --> C[3·Build] --> D[4·Infra]
    D --> E[5·Platform] --> F[6·Deploy] --> G[7·Agent]
    G --> H[8·Verify] --> I[9·TearDown]
```

> **Pre-reqs (all paths):** Docker ≥ 24 + Compose v2. Path A also needs Rust stable, `sqlx-cli`, and `trunk`. Path B also needs `cloudflared` installed on the demo server. Path C just needs Docker.

---

# Path A · Local Dev (cold machine → torn down)

## A.1 · Clean

```bash
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml down -v --remove-orphans
docker builder prune -af && docker image prune -af
for r in atelier-proto atelier-sdk atelier-backend atelier-webapp; do
  (cd ~/git/iteralabs/$r && cargo clean)
done
```

List the usage of the ports.

```bash
sudo ss -tulpn
```

In case postgreSQL is running in the background as a system default

```bash
sudo systemctl stop postgresql
sudo systemctl disable postgresql
```

## A.2 · Configure with either the `source .env` or the following:

```bash
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra
SECRET=$(openssl rand -base64 48)
cat > .env <<EOF
# --- Port Config --- #
WEBAPP_PUBLIC_PORT=3000      # cloudflared/config.yml iteralabs.xyz/* → :3000
GATEWAY_GRPC_PORT=50051      # cloudflared/config.yml gateway.iteralabs.xyz → :50051
GATEWAY_HEALTH_PORT=8082

# --- Internal only
OVERSEER_REST_PORT=8000      # webapp nginx proxies to it
OVERLEDGER_PORT=8090
POSTGRES_PORT=5432
KAFKA_PORT=9092
KAFKA_L_PORT=29092
ZOOKEEPER_CLIENT_PORT=2181
ZOOKEEPER_TICK_TIME=2000

# --- Secrets Config --- #
GATEWAY_JWT_SECRET=UvzuM91Qga3k+EALnEHPu02RyHXP81gmV9ZpD4KILdnlMmQSZT3ZCcGg66wyT6iv
JWT_SECRET=$GATEWAY_JWT_SECRET

# --- Usability configs for DEMO --- #
AUTH_DEV_BYPASS=true
BINDING_PENDING_GRACE_MS=600000

# --- Logs config --- #
RUST_LOG=atelier_overseer=debug,atelier_gateway=debug,info,sqlx=warn
EOF
```

- `BINDING_PENDING_GRACE_MS=600000` (10 min) keeps the §1.8.1 grace ticker from sweeping a 
Pending Binding while staging the agent. Production: `60000`. 
- Both `GATEWAY_JWT_SECRET` and `JWT_SECRET` must hold the **same** 
value — the gateway and overseer sign / validate against it.

## A.3 · Build

Build everything from the docker-compose-beta.yml

```bash
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up --build -d
```

After a succesfull run, it should show five additions: 

- 5432 (postgres, docker proxy)
- 8000 (overseer)
- 8082 (gateway healthz)
- 50051 (gateway gRPC)
- 3000 (webapp). 
- 9092 (kafka)

At that point the public curl -vI https://gateway.iteralabs.xyz 
will return something other than 502 and the BYO end-to-end test becomes runnable.

This is an example, IPv6 and IPv4 might change
```bash
* Host gateway.iteralabs.xyz:443 was resolved.
* IPv6: 2606:4700:3036::ac43:a4e8, 2606:4700:3037::6815:39a3
* IPv4: 172.67.164.232, 104.21.57.163
*   Trying [2606:4700:3036::ac43:a4e8]:443...
* Connected to gateway.iteralabs.xyz (2606:4700:3036::ac43:a4e8) port 443
```

Generate the lockfile for sharing it cross layers in docker build.

```bash
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-sdk   && cargo generate-lockfile
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-proto && cargo generate-lockfile
```

Build atelier-agent

```bash
docker build -f ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra/dockerfiles/agent.Dockerfile \
    -t iteralabs/atelier-agent:latest ~/git/iteralabs
```

The last line builds the agent image used in §A.7 (and consumed verbatim by Path C end-users). 
The agent is intentionally **not** a workspace member of `atelier-sdk` — its Dockerfile uses a 
standalone `cd atelier-sdk/atelier-agent && cargo build --release` with 
`CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/app/atelier-sdk/target` for shared cache. See `agent.Dockerfile` header note.

## A.4 · Boot Individual Components of the Infra

### Selective building

In case that the preference is to build only the database.

```bash
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up -d postgres
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up postgres-init
```

To build only the Internal Message Broker with Kafka and Zookeeper.

```bash
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up -d zookeeper kafka
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up kafka-init
```

The following command must list 7 topics: 

- `lifecycle.events`
- `control.manifests`
- `control.commands`
- `telemetry.reports`
- `artifact.frames`
- `dataset.events`
- `events.bus`

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml exec kafka \
  kafka-topics --bootstrap-server kafka:29092 --list
```

To Boot the Gateway and the Overseer backend services together.

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up -d gateway overseer
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml logs -f gateway overseer
```

And to Boot the WebApp (FrontEnd)

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up -d webapp
```

Wait for `availability matrix: Ready` (overseer) and `gRPC listening on 0.0.0.0:50051` (gateway). 
No `BrokerTransportFailure` loops. Webapp lands at `http://localhost:3000`.

