## B.8 · Operations on Ultradian

**Update the platform** (after `git pull` brings in new code):

```bash
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml build gateway overseer
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up -d gateway overseer

cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-webapp
./deploy/deploy-lan.sh 8080            # rebuilds + redeploys with zero-downtime-ish swap

# Tunnel restart only needed if you changed ingress rules
sudo systemctl restart cloudflared
```

**Auto-restart on Ultradian reboot.** Already covered:
- Backend containers: `restart: unless-stopped` is set in `docker-compose.beta.yml`.
- Webapp container: same flag set by `deploy-lan.sh` (`--restart unless-stopped`).
- Tunnel: `sudo cloudflared service install` (B.5.f) made it a systemd unit.

**Logs and health:**

```bash
docker compose -f ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra/docker-compose.beta.yml logs -f overseer gateway
docker logs -f atelier                              # webapp container
sudo journalctl -u cloudflared -f --since '5 min ago'
curl -sf http://localhost:8000/health
curl -sf https://www.iteralabs.xyz/atelier/ -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}\n'
```

**Rotating the JWT signing key** (revokes all outstanding agent tokens):

```bash
cd ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra
SECRET=$(openssl rand -base64 48)
sed -i "s|^GATEWAY_JWT_SECRET=.*|GATEWAY_JWT_SECRET=$SECRET|" .env
sed -i "s|^JWT_SECRET=.*|JWT_SECRET=$SECRET|" .env
docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up -d --force-recreate gateway overseer
```

All currently-running agent containers will start failing JWT validation; redeploy services from the dashboard to mint fresh tokens.

**Stop everything cleanly:**

```bash
docker stop atelier                                 # webapp
docker compose -f ~/git/iteralabs/atelier-infra/docker-compose.beta.yml down
sudo systemctl stop cloudflared
```

Add `-v` to the `docker compose down` to drop Postgres and Kafka volumes (destroys all session/binding/agent state).

