# Path C · End-User Agent Quickstart

You (the researcher) just got a credential block from the webapp's SpawnModal after clicking Deploy. It looks like:

```bash
docker run -d --rm \
  --add-host=host.docker.internal:host-gateway \
  -e ATELIER_GATEWAY_URL=https://gateway.iteralabs.xyz \
  -e ATELIER_TOKEN=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1Qi… \
  iteralabs/atelier-agent:latest
```

That snippet is **almost** what you want — three additions for a real research workflow:

## C.1 · Pull the agent image

```bash
docker pull iteralabs/atelier-agent:latest
```

(Until the image is published to a registry, the platform operator hands it to you via `docker save | docker load` or you build from source per Path A §A.3.)

## C.2 · Pick a host directory for Parquet output

```bash
mkdir -p ~/atelier-data && chmod 0777 ~/atelier-data
```

The container writes to `/data` internally; mount your host directory there.

## C.3 · Run the agent with the volume mount

```bash
docker run -d --rm \
  --name atelier-agent \
  --add-host=host.docker.internal:host-gateway \
  -v ~/atelier-data:/data \
  -e ATELIER_GATEWAY_URL=https://gateway.iteralabs.xyz \
  -e ATELIER_TOKEN=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1Qi…  \
  -e RUST_LOG=info \
  iteralabs/atelier-agent:latest
```

The two changes from the SpawnModal snippet:
- `-v ~/atelier-data:/data` — Parquet files land here on your machine.
- `--name atelier-agent` — easier to stop later.

## C.4 · Verify

```bash
docker logs -f atelier-agent
```

Within a few seconds you should see:

```
INFO atelier_connect::remote_agent::gateway: Registration accepted — agent_id allocated by Gateway
INFO atelier_connect::workers::market_worker: subscribed to BTCUSDT@depth20@100ms
```

Within a flush window (default 200 snapshots ≈ 20s), Parquet files appear:

```bash
ls ~/atelier-data/BTCUSDT/orderbooks/    # → binance_BTCUSDT_ob_sync_<ts>.parquet
ls ~/atelier-data/BTCUSDT/trades/         # → binance_BTCUSDT_trades_sync_<ts>.parquet
```

Read into Python / Polars / DuckDB:

```python
import pyarrow.parquet as pq
df = pq.read_table('~/atelier-data/BTCUSDT/orderbooks/binance_BTCUSDT_ob_sync_<ts>.parquet').to_pandas()
print(df.head())
```

The dashboard at `https://www.iteralabs.xyz/atelier/` shows your agent's live KPIs (messages/sec, total events, uptime) within seconds of registration.

## C.5 · Stop the agent

From the webapp: click Delete on the service. The agent self-exits when its binding terminates.

From your terminal: `docker stop atelier-agent`. The platform sees the heartbeat stop and reaps the binding within the reconnect grace window.

## C.6 · Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Check |
|---|---|
| `Registration rejected — UNAUTHENTICATED` | Token expired or wrong gateway URL. Get fresh credentials from SpawnModal. |
| Agent connects but no data | Verify the manifest's symbol exists on the exchange (Binance spot pairs only — USDT-M futures and Bybit are deferred). |
| No Parquet files after 30s | The volume mount might not have write access. `ls -la ~/atelier-data` should show world-writable; otherwise `chmod 0777`. |
| `cannot connect to gateway` | If you're behind a corporate firewall, port 50051 may be blocked. The Cloudflare Tunnel HTTPS ingress (B.5) helps. |
| Dashboard shows no agent after `docker run` | Confirm the agent container is actually running: `docker ps`. If it exited, `docker logs atelier-agent` will show why. |

